Aspose.CAD for .NET is a class library that enables your applications to perform a great range of drawings processing tasks. Aspose.CAD supports DXF, DWG, DGN, DWF, IFC, STL, DWT and other CAD formats. With Aspose.CAD you can modify, convert, render and print documents without utilizing Autodesk AutoCAD®.

Aspose.CAD for .NET is well documented to help you create your solutions on different platforms.

Rich Set of Features

Aspose.CAD for .NET features can be divided into two main areas:
 - Conversions: High quality conversions to Pdf, Bmp, Gif, Jpeg, Jpeg2000, Png, Wmf, Tiff, Psd formats
 - Document Object Model: Programmatic access through a rich API to all drawing elements allows to modify, extract, copy, split, join, and replace drawing content

Platform Independence

You can use Aspose.CAD for .NET to build any type of a 32-bit or 64-bit .NET application including ASP.NET, WCF, WinForms, .NET Standard.

Performance and Scalability

Aspose.CAD is designed to perform great both on a server or client. Aspose.CAD is a single .NET assembly that can be deployed with any .NET application by simply copying it. You do not have to worry about any other services or modules. You can literally generate thousands of images in minutes with Aspose.CAD and that involves opening a drawing, modifying content or populating it with data and saving it. Even most of the complex drawings are opened and saved on a P4 2.4Ghz 1Gb RAM machine in a second.

Aspose.CAD is multithread safe as long as only one thread works on a drawing at a time. It is a typical scenario to have one thread working on one drawing. Different threads can safely work on different drawings at the same time.

Free support for Aspose.CAD for .NET is provided on our support forum:
https://forum.aspose.com/ 
and on StackOverflow:
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/aspose.cad
summary: Aspose.CAD for .NET is a class library for .NET that enables you to perform a wide range of drawing processing tasks directly within your applications.

GroupDocs.Comparison for .NET is a lightweight library which allows you to merge and compare two versions of a PDF or Office document and display differences between them.

GroupDocs.Comparison is a one-stop solution for comparing documents of all common formats. It can be used to generate diffs for PDF files, Microsoft Word documents (DOC, DOCX), Excel spreadsheets (XLS, XSLSX), PowerPoint presentations (PPT, PPTX), TXT and HTML documents.

GroupDocs.Comparison works without any external dependencies and can be deployed with just a single DLL. There is no need to install any 3rd party software on the server or the client side. We also provide a C# demo, to help you explore the library quickly.
      
The product has the following key features:
	- Native support for the following formats: PDF files, Microsoft Word documents (DOC, DOCX), Excel spreadsheets (XLS, XSLSX), PowerPoint presentations (PPT, PPTX), TXT and HTML
	- Ability to compare file parts separately: pages, slides, paragraphs, worksheets
	- Ability to get object model of the comparison  results
	- Flexible comparison API that provides both unified API for all formats and format specific API.
	- Apply/Discard changes support for all supported formats
    - Designed as native .NET library which allow usage in all possible project types
    - Improved comparison performance

For more details on the library, please visit GroupDocs website at:
https://products.groupdocs.com/comparison/net

Note: The library comes up with some limitations in the evaluation mode. In order to test full features of GroupDocs.Viewer for .NET library, please request a free 30-day temporary license.
